description:
Responsibilities

About TikTok:
TikTok is the leading destination for short-form mobile video. Our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. TikTok has global offices including Los Angeles, New York, London, Paris, Berlin, Dubai, Mumbai, Singapore, Jakarta, Seoul, and Tokyo.

The Talent Acquisition Center - International was established in 2020, and aims at providing recruitment solutions & deliveries across the world for different business units at TikTok outside China sustainably. Our mission is boost efficiency, enhance globalization and pursue sustainable development.
TikTok is committed to creating an inclusive space where employees are valued for their skills, experiences, and unique perspectives. Our platform connects people from across the globe and so does our workplace. At TikTok, our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. To achieve that goal, we are committed to celebrating our diverse voices and to creating an environment that reflects the many communities we reach. We are passionate about this and hope you are too.

Cooperate with the HR/recruiting team to understand HR program requirements and team goals by applying creativity and innovation to support the fast-paced HR team globally;
Collect valid data and analyze hiring funnels to ensure recruiting health and help with hiring efficiency improvements;
Coordinate with cross-functional teams to better support global recruiting excellence;
Assist with performance review of employees and the implementation of employee care activities;
Support on recruiting issues if neccesary.
Qualifications
Prefer students who graduate in 2022 or 2023;
Demonstrate interest in human resource field. Keen to connect with people;
Fluent in reading, writing and oral English, multilingual ability is a plus;
Great communicator and team player;
Proven ability to develop sound research methodologies and collect, synthesize, analyze, and interpret data.

Founded in 2015 in Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam, Ahamove is an on-demand logistics service based on the concept of a shared economy, providing customers to fill excess capacity for logistics suppliers and reduce costs for consumers.
You can find more about us at Facebook case study, Harvard case study, and on Asia Nikkei news.
This is a tremendous opportunity to take your career to the next level. Please review the information below and if you are interested, follow the Apply instructions.
Job Description
Support team in all activities of the recruitment process such as: posting jobs on recruitment websites, contacting candidates, welcoming candidates, arranging tests and scheduling interviews, data entry, etc;
Join the recruitment process for both non-technical positions;
Build up candidates database;
Other administrative requirements from the supervisor..
Job Requirements
Priority to final year students or fresh graduates with preferred majors in Human Resources, Communications, Business Administration, or business-related degrees;
Have strong communication skills, systematic thinking, and attention to detail;
Have a responsible and positive work attitude with good abilities to deal with challenging tasks in a fast-paced environment.
Why it would be awesome to work with us
We recognize that the role of HR also contributes to the growth of the company by finding talent and nurturing them.
You will get hands-on experience in jobs such as recruitment, business partner, and operations.
You will be directly responsible for the assigned work and provide suggestions for improvement.

RESPONSIBILITIES:
Go deep into the business department, understand the business strategy and goals, take the initiative to obtain the human resources demands of the business department, and be responsible for the local personnel work in Vietnam;
Provide human resources support for the development of business departments, including personnel attendance, recruitment, training, performance appraisal, etc.;
According to the situation of the team of the business department, clarify the team competency quality model, design the growth path and training plan of personnel, effectively formulate and implement the talent development plan and follow up the implementation;
Promote the promotion of the company's system and culture through communication and interaction with management and employees;
Responsible for the administrative affairs of the department.
REQUIREMENTS:
Bachelor degree or above, major in human resource management; Familiarity with Vietnamese is an advantage;
More than 5 years of overseas local manpower recruitment and management experience, working experience in large manufacturing companies, bicycles, electric bicycle industry experience is preferred;
Have strong resource co-ordination ability, strong ability to work under pressure, and service awareness;
Proficient in using office software, including word, excel, ppt, etc.;
Good at communication and coordination, care for the physical and mental health of employees;
For more information, please contact
Ms. Hoang Lan Huong (84) 24 3936 7618 - Ext: 141
Email: hoang.lan.huong@talentnet.vn

Mô tả công việc
On April 20th 2022, Vingroup signed a comprehensive cooperation agreement with the UK‘s leading education system Brighton College to establish Brighton College Vietnam.
Brighton College Vietnam at Vinhomes Ocean Park, Hanoi is now open for admissions for the 2023-2024 academic year from grade 1 to grade 10 (from 5 to 16 years old). This is the first campus to be established under the partnership between Vingroup and Brighton College, an UK’s top private school with nearly 200 years of history.
We are looking for talents for a variety of positions at the school.

Work location: Brighton College Vietnam, Vinhomes Ocean Park Urban Area, Da Ton Commune, Gia Lam District, Hanoi.
1. JOB DESCRIPTION
Develop headcount and recruitment plan on an annual basis;
Ensure effective recruitment according to the approved plan;
Implement recruitment advertising and manage BCVN’s recruitment channels;
Develop and manage the recruitment budget;
Monitor new hire reception and onboarding.
2. REQUIREMENTS
Bachelor’s degree or higher in Economics, Business, English Studies or Human Resources Management;
Proficiency in all 04 English language skills;
At least 03 years of experience in recruitment for both foreign and Vietnamese employees; experience in recruitment for foreign teacher, experience in international education environments is a plus;
Good communication skills;
Good service thinking, professional manners and strong self-confidence;
Effective organizational and problem solving skills;
Flexibility and ability to work under high pressure.
3. BENEFITS
Negotiable,competitive salary;
Insurance plan according to the law and a separate Vingroup health insurance package;
Incentives on Vingroup’s services;
Promotion and self-development opportunities;
Opportunity to work in a professional, dynamic and challenging international education environment;
Chances to learn and grow by working with the world’s leading educators.
4. HOW TO APPLY: Please leave your application information below, together with a CV in English.
Brighton College Vietnam places safeguarding of its pupils as its highest priority and as such references will be taken up before interviews and the successful applicant will be subject to appropriate qualification checks and police checks as to their suitability to work with children. Appropriate safeguarding and safer recruitment questions will form part of the selection process.

Nộp đơn ứng tuyển

Lương: Thỏa Thuận
Location: Hà Nội
Hạn nộp hồ sơ: 15/08 — 30/11/2023

