Lương: Thỏa Thuận
Location: Hà Nội
Hạn nộp hồ sơ: 01/08 — 30/11/2023

Responsibilities
TikTok is the leading destination for short-form mobile video. Our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. TikTok has global offices including Los Angeles, New York, London, Paris, Berlin, Dubai, Singapore, Jakarta, Seoul and Tokyo.

Why Join Us
At TikTok, our people are humble, intelligent, compassionate and creative. We create to inspire - for you, for us, and for more than 1 billion users on our platform. We lead with curiosity and aim for the highest, never shying away from taking calculated risks and embracing ambiguity as it comes. Here, the opportunities are limitless for those who dare to pursue bold ideas that exist just beyond the boundary of possibility. Join us and make impact happen with a career at TikTok.

About the Team:
The HR Operations team endeavours to continuously build and deliver a seamless and positive employee experience across the whole employee lifecycle. We're dedicated to leading with care and have empathy in mind. We strive to develop efficient and simple people processes, systems, policies and programs. We aspire to ensure employees feel heard and that they are given the appropriate resources and support needed to be effective and efficient during their career. The ideal candidate is someone who is highly motivated with a positive attitude, and exhibits patience, teamwork, critical thinking, and emotional intelligence.

You will provide support and knowledge to businesses for the whole employee lifecycle. Continually work on the enhancement of the employee lifecycle through process improvements, automation.

Responsibilities:
1. Enhance the people and workplace experience through localized people initiatives throughout the employee lifecycle, including visa matters, process improvements, data & insights;
2. Provide support and knowledge to the business for the whole employee lifecycle. Continually, work on the enhancement of the employee lifecycle and be a trusted advisor to internal and external stakeholders;
3. Help scale various HR programs to create efficient and simple people processes, systems, policies, and programs;
4. Maintain partnerships with geographically distributed HRBPs, TA and other HR Operations team members;
5. Exercise independent judgment and discretion do determine appropriate actions or solutions to problems;
6. Build and develop strong lasting stakeholder relationships with key departments across the business by providing accurate, timely and appropriate advice.
Qualifications
1. Advantageous to have 3+ years of People Operations/Human Resources related experience.
2. Strong knowledge of labour/compliance laws and cultural nuances within Vietnam and experience in setting up & handling trade union in Vietnam;
3. Experience with employee lifecycle (onboarding, transfers, performance cycles, leaves of absence, immigration matters and offboarding);
4. Support employees and improve employee experience by providing end to end HR solution to solve their issues;
5. High level of discretion, confidentiality, and ethics.
6. Humility, flexibility, and good interpersonal & customer facing skills are a must to be part of a strong and united team across APAC;
7. Highly proficient and excellent communication skills in English.

TikTok is committed to creating an inclusive space where employees are valued for their skills, experiences, and unique perspectives. Our platform connects people from across the globe and so does our workplace. At TikTok, our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. To achieve that goal, we are committed to celebrating our diverse voices and to creating an environment that reflects the many communities we reach. We are passionate about this and hope you are too.

HR Manager are involved with recruitment, training, career development, compensation and benefits, employee relations, industrial relations, employment law, compliance, disciplinary and grievance issues, redundancies etc. The most important role is to ensure the company culture and values are well spread through the company and enable staff to be the best of them.
Develop and implement HR strategies and initiatives aligned with the overall business strategy;
Manage the recruitment and selection process;
Maintain pay plan and benefits program;
Assess training needs to apply and monitor training programs;
Assist with the performance management and review process;
Organize office operations and procedures;
Nurture a positive working environment;
Ensure legal compliance throughout human resource management.
Yêu cầu công việc
Experience in design & build industry could be an advantage;
Degree in human resources management or equivalent.
Interest in human development and company culture building.
Experience in human resources or related field.
Ability to build and maintain positive relationships with colleagues.
Experience in educating and coaching staff.
Experience in following and maintaining workplace privacy.
Knowledge of relevant health and safety laws.
Good communication in English.

I. RESPONSIBILITIES
– Be a member of the CEO Assistant Board, report directly to the CEO and work directly with the BOD of GHTK’s Departments;
– Participate and be responsible for the tasks assigned by the CEO in business activities, operations, project development and development of new products and services of GHTK according to personal strengths and specialities:
+ Business Development: Develop GHTK’s services in E-logistics, Fintech based on creative business ideas, optimize GHTK’s strategic orientations and goals in each stage, maximize company’s profits; or
+ Project Management: Participate and Promote the effectiveness of operation projects: Create plans, ensure resources, project operation, , risk management, efficiency promotion; or
+ HR Strategy: Optimize and develope human resources; or
+ Product Owner: Plan and develop software products: User Research, work with UX/UI Designer, responsible for product life cycle, product launching, product development and improvement.
– Consult and advise the CEO in setting development strategies, goals.
– Other duties as assigned.
II. REQUIREMENTS
– Having work experience with BoD as senior/manager in big corporations in relevant fields: Technology, Finance, Logistic, Services, E-Commerce, Economics, Human Resources;
– Working experience for start-up or companies with effective business models is an advantage;
– Have good knowledge and mindset about strategy & operational management in large-scale organizations;
– Can-do spirit and always ready for new challenges;
– Computer proficiency: word-processing, Microsoft Office, and data base management;
– Self-motivated, result-oriented with high standards, proactive and reach the core of the problems to achieve the highest level of efficiency; open-minded thinking for innovation and creativity; ability to grasp trends quickly;
– Ability to work independently while maintaining effective working relationships with CEO, managers, co-workers, supervisors…
III. BENEFITS
– Salary: up to $3000, based on performance and responsibility. Bonus per project and special occasions;
– Benefits in accordance with current Law;
– Premium health insurance for yourself and family member;
– A young, dynamic and supportive working environment with start-up spirit and promotion opportunities, creating a sustainable career path in the E-logistics field;
– Be empowered, self-determined, and have enough space for self-development in a typical E-logistics environment.
IV. OTHER INFORMATION
– Working time: Monday – Saturday morning, 9:00 am – 6:30 pm.
– Address: GHTK Building, No. 8 Pham Hung street, Me Tri ward, Nam Tu Liem district, Ha Noi.
V. HOW TO APPLY
To apply for the Executive Assistant to CEO position, please send us your Resume to email talent.acquisition@ghtk.co
Subject mail: CEOO – Fullname.

At Zalo, we believe Vietnamese engineers can build world-class technology products. As a market leader of a product ecosystem with million users in Vietnam, we build and develop a workplace where responsible, passionate, and dynamic talents thrive. We look forward to working with you to grow vigorously while keep improving your quality of living thanks to working with the best talents, on most successful brands, and in sizable projects that improve millions of Vietnamese lives.
Zalo is seeking an experienced and results-driven Learning & Development Lead to align our HR initiatives and functions with business objectives and business needs.
What you will do
Assesses training and development needs through surveys, interviews, focus groups, and communication with managers, instructors, etc.;
Creates, organizes, plans, and presents various forms of onboarding, orientation, and skills training for employees and customers;
Develops unique training programs to fulfill workers specific needs to maintain or improve job skills;
Creates and/or acquires training procedure manuals, guides, and course materials;
Presents training and development programs using various forms and formats, including group discussion, lectures, simulations, and videos;
Maintains records of training and development activities, attendance, results of tests and assessments, and retraining requirements;
Assesses training materials prepared by instructors;
Evaluates program effectiveness through assessments, surveys, and feedback;
Maintains knowledge of the latest trends in training and development;
Prepares and implements training budget; maintains records and reports of expenses;
Performs other related duties as required.
What you will need
Bachelor’s degree in Business, Human resources, or a related field required;
At least 5 years of training experience with expertise in instructional design;
Proficient with Microsoft Office Suite and related program software;
Fluent in English;
Structured thinker;
Ability to work efficiently under high pressure.
Preferred Qualifications:
Passionate about Zalo products;
Interest in data and technology;
Ability to e-learning design.

Ninja Van is a tech-enabled logistics company on a mission to provide hassle-free delivery services for businesses of all sizes across Southeast Asia. Launched in 2014, we started operations in Singapore and have become the region's largest and fastest growing last-mile logistics company, partnering with over 35,000 merchants and delivering more than 1,000 parcels every minute across six countries.

At our core, we are a technology company that is disrupting a massive industry with cutting-edge software and operational concepts. Powered by algorithm-based optimisation, dynamic routing, end-to-end tracking and a data-driven approach, we provide best-of-class delivery services that delight both the shippers and end customers. But we are just getting started! We have much room for improvement and many ideas that will further shape the industry.
Key Accountabilities
Payroll, PIT & SHUI:
1. Payroll·
Running monthly payroll by computing the attendance record and leave, calculating the monthly bonuses, overtime, and social benefits for eligible employees, updating new hires and resigns, etc...;
Arranging for pay bank transfers and distribution of pay slips;
Proceeding all required payroll reports.
2. PIT:
Monitoring the PIT annual settlements;
Dealing with Tax Officers and auditors in PIT issues;
Controlling PIT costs monthly and yearly;
Providing updated legal regulations and laws in relation to PIT.
3. SHUI:
Ensure all the submissions related to SHUI are done properly;
Give the solution to any issues that happened and lead the team to take action;
Controlling Social insurance costs monthly and yearly.
Employee Data Management:
Collect and maintain confidential employment-related records, files, and reports, … according to policy and legal requirements;
Follow up probation evaluations, and contract renewal evaluations, and prepare labor contracts within the required time frame;
Prepare documents in relation to employees (i.e. promotion, demotion, termination, certificates, etc.) ensuring high standard quality and timeliness criteria are always met;
Play the administration role in the HRIS system.
Annual Budget And manpower Cost:
Calculating the annual HR budget and people cost of all companies;
Controlling the actual people cost of departments vs annual budget;
To take responsibility for explaining to the Finance department issues actual people cost, budget cost, PIT cost, and SI cost.
Labor Contracts:
Manage all kinds of labor contracts for new staff (probation/labor/seasonal) & renewal labor contracts;
Make an addendum to the labor contracts (if any);
Proceed with all documentation for resignation (contract termination decision, contract liquidation minutes), and ensure all resignation cases are addressed in compliance with the company’s regulations;
Ensure all kinds of labor contracts are given to employees on time.
Team Management
Train, coach and develop subordinates by progressively transferring knowledge for career development and succession planning;
Contribute to building HR’s culture and driving positive change whenever applicable.
Requirements:
5 years or more of experience in compensation and benefits or human resources. Relevant work experience in designated compensation and benefits;
Up-to-date knowledge of labor law, social and health insurance, unemployment insurance, and PIT;
Able to run Payroll Software;
Good at excel skills;
Knowledge of compensation & benefits disciplines, concepts, and theories.
Fluent English.
Benefit
Working address: Ninja Van Vietnam Office, Tan Binh District, Ho Chi Minh city.

Salary and benefits:
Competitive income compared to the market
"Tet" bonus, Performance review from 1 - 4 months
Paid social insurance based on full salary
12 days annual leave, 5 days sick leave (with full salary)
High-class AON Health Insurance for manager level.
Year End Party, annual Townhall Ceremony
Annual company trip
Attractive team-building activities, regular internal activities
Provide laptops for employees

Training and developing:
Participate in internal training courses: online/offline
Opportunities to promote to higher positions: Senior, Team Leader, Manager, etc.

Work environment & colleagues:
Senior leaders are open-minded, respectful, and ready to facilitate personal growth;
Young and dynamic working environment;
Scope of work is large, the company has more than 6000 employees, and the company has operations spreading to 63 provinces/cities thoughout the country.

Submit a job application
