SCOPE OF WORK

Chief Engineer will be responsible to Property Manager for the implementation, management and supervision of the maintenance activities of the building from outside to inside but not limited to the fields of electricity, piping water & drainage, grounding, energy saving and other maintenance tasks required to maintain operations in optimum and efficient conditions while ensuring safety and compliance for residents. and staff.
Asset management and building safety
Ensure proper use of the safety regulations inside the building;
Ensure that property of residents in the building is not damaged by outside agents;
Ensure all damages and potential problems reported, repair and maintenance related issues are promptly dealt with;
Plan and participate in fire drills, monitor fire equipment.
Human Resources
Support HR Department in interviewing technical staff;
Develop and maintain professional training programs for the technical department;
Train technical staff when needed;
Advise employees on work-related matters;
Ensure all staff maintain proper appearance, personal hygiene, proper uniforms and name badges;
Train/ tutor for all staff on new processes;
Train for all employees in safety and emergencies;
Maintain and operate all M&E systems including air conditioners, generators, chilling systems, ventilation etc. and distribution systems of electricity, water etc. to make sure they all work in good condition;
Supervise and coordinate matters carried out by external contractors under contract, service agreement and warranty contract;
Ensure timely response to service requests from residents, employees and managers related to the issue of repair or replacement of furniture or interior decoration.
Subcontractors
Check and resolve contract issues with subcontractors;
Submit the contract to Property Manager for approval;
Assist and supervise the contractor as they are working in the building, ensure everything is clean after work, safe and smooth;
Supervise and check the work to make sure the contractor is doing well.
Financial
Prepare an annual budget for the technical department;
Monitor payroll and productivity to ensure all employees meet the essential job requirements;
Establish and evaluate thermal, electrical power, repair and maintenance to achieve optimum capacity and cost within permissible levels;
Control and maintain inventory including parts, tools and supplies;
Reduce spending and control wast
Others
Implement the department's policies and procedures as instructed by Property Manager;
Establish and maintain effective channels of communication between operations department, e.g. customer service, hygiene, and security;
Continuously review existing systems/ business processes and propose methods for improvement based on existing service standards and corresponding changes;
Supervise and take responsibility for department training, ensuring operational standards are always met;
Ensure flexible working hours based on existing operating requirements;
Perform any other duties assigned by Property Manager.
Requirement
Education
University degree or above majoring in Electrical, Industrial Electricity, Refrigeration, Mechanical & Electrical or relevant fields.
Skills and Qualifications
Proven experienced in manage Technician team as strategic leader that deliver high performance.
Execellent leadership & team management skills with work performance optimization.
Excellent in communication, problem – solving skills
Strong knowledge about technology related to saving & using effectively energy, water.
Experience
At least 3- 5 years experience in Chief Engineer role.
Computer Skills
Proficient in Microsoft Office (MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint)
